All roads lead to Ikenne Remo, Ogun State today as the late Mr. Olutayo Michael Oreselu popularly known as Baba Alagbede, is bided a final farewell. Oreselu, who died recently after a brief illness, was aged 110. On Monday, January 23, the funeral ceremony commenced with a Service of Songs conducted by the Redeemed Christian Church of God (RCCG) at his residence, 46, Alhaji Amoo Street, Ojota, Lagos.  This was followed by Lying in State and Christian Wake Keep at his hometown residence, 4, Ilisan Road, Ikenne Remo, Ogun State on Thursday, January 26, 2023. However, the funeral service will hold at 10 a.m. today at Our Saviour’s Anglican Church, Ikenne Remo, Ogun State, while reception of guests will take place immediately after the service at Obafemi Awolowo Square (Recreation Center), Ikenne Remo, Ogun State.  Pa Oreselu was survived by children, grandchildren, and great grandchildren.